headlines.title: US-China trade talks: Countries agree on plan to ease export controls after meeting in London
headlines.description: The United States and China have agreed on a framework to implement their trade truce, officials on both sides said Wednesday, after concluding two days of talks in London to defuse tensions and ease export restrictions that threaten to disrupt global manufacturing.

headlines.title: Car plows through Chicago protest as thousands rally in solidarity with L.A. anti-ICE demonstrations
headlines.description: A vehicle was seen speeding through the crowd and several protesters were detained during the Tuesday demonstration that drew thousands to downtown Chicago, voicing opposition to the Trump administration's stepped-up use of force against immigrants.

headlines.title: USMNT vs. Switzerland score: USA soccer's shocking blowout loss to Switzerland by the numbers
headlines.description: The U.S. conceded all four goals in the first half of the blowout loss as the vibes remain very poor

headlines.title: Roman Anthony's first MLB hit is a 2-run double that propels Red Sox past Rays
headlines.description: Baseball's No. 1 prospect now has his first MLB hit.

headlines.title: USMNT humiliated by Switzerland 4-0; Pochettino’s squad loses fourth straight
headlines.description: It's back to the drawing board for this USMNT group, which fell behind 4-0 by halftime in a putrid performance.

headlines.title: Trump Tariffs Can Stay in Effect Longer, Appeals Court Says
headlines.description: Donald Trump can continue to enforce his global tariffs for now, a federal appeals court held in a win for the president on one of his signature economic policies.

headlines.title: U.S. and China Agree to Stick to Prior Trade Truce After Tensions Escalated
headlines.description: Two days of talks resulted in a “framework” that is intended to solidify terms of a deal the superpowers reached in Geneva last month.

headlines.title: Immigration officials raid Omaha meat plant
headlines.description: Immigration authorities have raided an Omaha meat production plant and detained dozens of workers. That prompted confusion from company officials who say they complied with the law and sparked protests outside the operation.

headlines.title: Stock market today: Live updates
headlines.description: The S&P 500 finished higher on Tuesday for a third straight session, with trade talks between the U.S. and China still ongoing in London.

headlines.title: US-China talks end with plan for Trump and Xi to approve
headlines.description: The US Commerce Secretary said the deal should result in some restrictions being resolved.
